abstract: G.M. said it sold 9,369,524 vehicles, a 3 percent increase. Toyota last week reported its sales as a rounded 9.37 million, 6 percent more than in 2006.
snippet: G.M. said it sold 9,369,524 vehicles, a 3 percent increase. Toyota last week reported its sales as a rounded 9.37 million, 6 percent more than in 2006.
lead_paragraph: DETROIT  General Motors and Toyota ended 2007 effectively tied in their fight to be the world’s largest automaker.

headline.main: G.M. and Toyota in a Close Race in ’07 Sales
